      %h1.mb-3 About OurGruuv
      %p.lead.mb-4
        Managers do one of the most important jobs in any company ... and most of them are asked to do it without clear tools. OurGruuv exists to change that.

      %section.mb-5
        %h2.h4.mb-3 Why this exists
        %p
          Early in my career I learned how much difference clear expectations make ... and how often recognition and feedback seem to follow vibes instead. When managers don't make “what good looks like” visible, growth can feel uneven in ways that are hard to name and harder to fix.
        %p
          Years later, in a conversation with the head of People at a previous company, the quarterly demographics report made a similar gap hard to ignore. Who was in the company and who held management seats did not match. The promotion pattern did not look like the workforce. The data was not a picture of fairness ... and vibes alone could not explain it.
        %p.mb-0
          That experience, a belief that managers deserve better tools, and an immediate need to build a layer of managers and calibrate how Product & Engineering would grow people ... that is what sparked the first version of
          %strong MAAP
          (a named subsystem inside OurGruuv for Milestones, Abilities, Assignments, Aspirations, and Positions). The personal why underneath it all:
          %em inspire and empower people to fulfill and go beyond their believed potential.

      %section.mb-5
        %h2.h4.mb-3 How we got here
        %p
          MAAP started as a practical answer to fairness and clarity: what does good look like in this role, what abilities unlock the next step, and how do we recognize growth without Hunger-Games merit theater?
        %p
          The thinking was shaped by growth frameworks that take ladders seriously ... including work from
          = link_to "Medium", "https://medium.com/s/engineering-growth-framework", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener"
          ,
          = link_to "Rent the Runway", "http://dresscode.renttherunway.com/blog/ladder", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener"
          ,
          = link_to "Spotify", "https://labs.spotify.com/2016/02/15/spotify-technology-career-steps/", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener"
          , and other skills matrices that treat expectations as something you can see and discuss.
        %p.mb-0
          That journey is captured in more depth in
          = link_to "An Essay about one man's journey towards Compensation Clarity", "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1jH2MGAXIGWOQmQSzq8HZRuDgz1TK5c3BQvEIrQnWudQ/edit?tab=t.0", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener"
          \... written as AR3's views on range, market, merit, and why organizations need a MAAP. OurGruuv is the product that grew from that conviction: clarity for teammates, calibration for managers, and systems that make recognition defensible instead of mysterious.

      %section.mb-5
        %h2.h4.mb-3 Jobs we're focused on
        %p.fw-semibold.mb-3
          Clarity leads to both personal and team growth.
        %p.text-muted.mb-3
          The work customers hire OurGruuv to do ... the same outcomes we measure as value:
        %ul.mb-0
          %li.mb-3
            %strong Capture our stories
            \... The foundation of clarity is communication. We help teams communicate with radical candor and nonviolent communication by capturing observation-based stories.
          %li.mb-3
            %strong Know where they stand
            \... The only thing worse than being surprised in a performance review is vague, unactionable feedback in that review. We help people get specific feedback they can act on through Performance Clarity Check-ins.
          %li.mb-3
            %strong Clarify growth paths
            \... Being clear about the behaviors, skills, and knowledge needed to exceed expectations drives continuous, predictable greatness. We help teammates get recognized for demonstrated growth through milestone achievements.
          %li.mb-3
            %strong Communicate real progress
            \... Goals you set and forget create the illusion of alignment. We help teams stay clear about why confidence is rising or falling so communication leads to real change.
          %li.mb-0
            %strong Equip managers ... and raise the ceiling
            \... Tools for one of the hardest, highest-leverage jobs in the company, with a through-line from New Us to every screen in OurGruuv: inspire and empower people to fulfill and go beyond their believed potential.

      %section.mb-5
        %h2.h4.mb-3 What's next
        %ul.mb-0
          %li Deepening the jobs above ... especially manager tools and continuous talent density.
          %li
            Growing
            = link_to "New Us", new_us_path
            with a People Partner co-founder and a small product crew.
          %li Keeping MAAP honest: public enough to inspire, rigorous enough to calibrate.

